The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Wednesday, February 18, 2004 				 AirTel offers more goodies 
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								New Delhi, Feb. 17: AirTel today reacted to the Reliance prepaid scheme that offers more talk-time at a lower processing fee, by revising talk-time upwards for its high denomination prepaid cards.																								AirTels revised scheme, Aisee Azadi Aur Kahan, which has come into effect from Monday midnight, will be available to all its 4.5 million prepaid customers. 																								The company will offer talk-time of Rs 3,000 on recharge coupons of Rs 3,240 denomination as against existing talk-time of Rs 2,700. The recharge coupon worth Rs 1,080 would give a talk-time of Rs 1,000 as against the existing talk-time worth Rs 850.																								All AirTel prepaid customers can now receive incoming calls and SMS in the first 15 days of the grace period. 																								Prepaid customers will also get the benefit of more grace period for three lower denomination coupons. 
